data.desc:
You're faced with a sample of materials you can touch.
→ Depending on how much you touch a sample, the human warmth/time you spend touching it (=the interest you show), different in-depth outputs appear: the first level is technical data, then a bit ambiguous, then something like 'traces of suffering and anxiety are detected in this material'.
//This can also be adapted to a display case: the material is in a display case and you have a glove you can touch it with.
